    "pathophysiology": "MPN stem cell mutation (JAK2/CALR/MPL) leads to clonal proliferation of megakaryocytes. These release fibrogenic cytokines (PDGF, TGF-beta, bFGF) causing bone marrow fibrosis. This forces extramedullary hematopoiesis in liver and spleen, leading to hepatomegaly with sinusoidal infiltration and portal hypertension. Hypersplenism causes hemolytic anemia contributing to jaundice. Transfusion iron overload adds hepatocellular injury. Eventually, the disease can transform to acute myeloid leukemia (blast phase).",
